WEBVTT

00:01.401 --> 00:02.902
<i>Previously, on "Being Mary Jane"...</i>

00:02.969 --> 00:05.905
<i>I'm not mad, I'm hurt.
I'm on this rollercoaster ride with you.</i>

00:05.972 --> 00:08.441
So, when you decide to jump off,
I feel the scrapes, too.

00:08.508 --> 00:11.010
I would like to formally welcome

00:11.077 --> 00:13.947
"Great Day USA's"
newest correspondent, Dani Hollins.

00:15.515 --> 00:16.549
<i>There was a guy.</i>

00:16.616 --> 00:18.818
<i>He only wanted help
getting his art out there.</i>

00:18.885 --> 00:20.687
You came to New York
to find a sugar daddy

00:20.754 --> 00:22.655
to solve your problems
and take care of you?

00:22.722 --> 00:24.791
Maybe it's time
to get real with yourself

00:24.858 --> 00:26.993
and find what makes you wanna get up.

00:27.060 --> 00:28.995
You two are involved, romantically.

00:29.062 --> 00:31.264
I'm taking you off her stories.
And there's more.

00:31.331 --> 00:33.333
Justin, I'm sending you to Kansas.

01:20.814 --> 01:23.883
Stay focused. Here we go.

01:26.252 --> 01:28.388
Let's see what's what.

01:45.772 --> 01:48.741
Amsterdam. Istanbul.

01:48.808 --> 01:49.943
Berlin.

01:50.009 --> 01:51.311
A typical producer.

01:51.878 --> 01:54.047
Kabul? Who'd you go to Kabul with?

02:05.525 --> 02:07.393
That's what I thought.

02:07.460 --> 02:08.628
Okay.

02:17.303 --> 02:18.838
One little look around won't hurt.

02:23.042 --> 02:24.444
Sorry not sorry, girl.

02:32.085 --> 02:33.353
You know that's right.

02:48.468 --> 02:49.669
Well...

02:49.736 --> 02:53.139
you can't fault a brother
for being prepared for the Apocalypse.

02:53.907 --> 02:56.109
Dork. Okay.

04:03.509 --> 04:04.844
Good morning.

04:04.911 --> 04:06.346
Hey, morning.

04:10.917 --> 04:13.686
What's got you going this early
and dressed up to boot?

04:13.753 --> 04:15.855
You know that old saying...

04:15.922 --> 04:17.724
the early bird gets the worm.

04:18.558 --> 04:20.627
Nobody's gonna help me be successful,

04:20.693 --> 04:22.695
so, I've gotta go get it.

04:23.529 --> 04:24.731
Is this about some guy?

04:24.797 --> 04:26.299
No, it's not about some guy.

04:26.933 --> 04:28.234
A job?

04:28.835 --> 04:31.037
Not just a job, a career.

04:32.572 --> 04:34.474
And what sparked this new attitude?

04:34.540 --> 04:36.676
I don't know. I guess...

04:36.743 --> 04:38.978
seeing New York,
spending time with Auntie.

04:39.045 --> 04:41.414
It just gave me a whole new perspective.

04:41.914 --> 04:43.416
I'm stepping into my destiny.

04:45.251 --> 04:48.821
Well, when you get to destiny,
pick up more half and half, this is bad.

04:51.391 --> 04:53.259
Hey, girl, guess what?

04:53.326 --> 04:56.129
That bullied cub scout that fought back,
I told his parents

04:56.195 --> 04:58.064
that he deserves to tell his story.

04:58.131 --> 05:01.267
We've got a full-fledged
social commentary on our hands now.

05:01.334 --> 05:02.535
Yes, mama!

05:04.303 --> 05:05.405
Okay.

05:05.471 --> 05:08.274
I mean, I'm all about more eyes on me,
but why the sudden push?

05:08.341 --> 05:10.343
Since Ronda dispelled those nasty rumors,

05:10.410 --> 05:12.679
they wanna promote GDU
as one big, happy family.

05:12.745 --> 05:14.681
I mean, we all can be related,

05:14.747 --> 05:15.982
except for Mary Jane.

05:16.049 --> 05:18.184
She could be our adopted
sister from Malawi.

05:18.251 --> 05:19.786
Your social media will blow up that.

05:24.791 --> 05:27.460
A closed-door conversation.
Am I being let go?

05:27.527 --> 05:29.262
No. No.

05:29.328 --> 05:32.231
- Then what did you want to talk about?
- Snooping.

05:32.298 --> 05:33.599
How far is too far?

05:34.734 --> 05:37.870
Lord. What did you do?

05:37.937 --> 05:41.340
I may have taken a box of keepsakes
from Justin's apartment.

05:41.407 --> 05:43.710
You didn't start
with misdemeanor snooping,

05:43.776 --> 05:45.311
you went to grand larceny.

05:45.378 --> 05:48.681
I only looked at, like, an eighth of it.

05:49.949 --> 05:51.117
Perhaps a third.

05:51.651 --> 05:53.486
- Perhaps.
- And what did you find?

05:53.553 --> 05:56.055
Okay, so, he dated this girl
named Simone for years,

05:56.122 --> 05:58.424
and he saved all
of the birthday cards she sent him.

05:58.491 --> 06:00.093
I didn't peg him as a romantic.

06:00.159 --> 06:03.629
I know, but he also may have
slept with his therapist.

06:03.696 --> 06:06.632
There was a letter. It was cryptic.
I'm not supposed to know this.

06:06.699 --> 06:09.869
You took a man's private belongings
and now you feel guilty.

06:09.936 --> 06:13.039
We have been together for weeks,
and I still feel like I don't know him.

06:13.106 --> 06:15.908
Put the box back and talk to him.

06:16.476 --> 06:18.177
- I will.
- When?

06:18.244 --> 06:20.379
- After you've looked everything?
- Basically.

06:20.446 --> 06:21.681
Immediately.

06:22.448 --> 06:25.418
And by the way, Mary Jane,
if you don't book my bartender Lorenzo,

06:25.485 --> 06:27.787
he won't be available
for your house warming.

06:27.854 --> 06:31.124
Right. Yeah. I can't do that party.

06:31.190 --> 06:32.291
Why not?

06:32.358 --> 06:35.561
You know how GDU is trying to sell
the whole one big happy family thing?

06:35.628 --> 06:38.164
And I thought, great,
I can invite my friends from work.

06:38.231 --> 06:40.767
Except now Justin's gone
and Kara's not talking to me,

06:40.833 --> 06:43.803
and my brother, PJ,
is trapped in Dubai somewhere.

06:43.870 --> 06:45.671
I have no buffers. I can't do it.

06:45.738 --> 06:47.840
It's a work party now. You can't cancel.

06:47.907 --> 06:49.275
Suck it up, girl.

06:49.342 --> 06:51.511
And it won't kill you
to plaster on that fake smile

06:51.577 --> 06:53.913
and play hostess for one night.

06:55.548 --> 06:58.084
- You do it every day at GDU.
- I sure do.

06:58.618 --> 07:01.154
- Watch me work.
- Right, then.

07:08.928 --> 07:10.997
I never expected to see you
back here, Niecy.

07:11.063 --> 07:12.298
I know, Claudia.

07:13.399 --> 07:14.867
I was wondering if we could talk.

07:24.610 --> 07:25.711
I don't have much time.

07:25.778 --> 07:29.282
That's okay.
Look, I just came here to apologize.

07:29.348 --> 07:31.918
I screwed up, major bad.

07:31.984 --> 07:33.953
Our agreement
was that you give me a booth

07:34.020 --> 07:35.788
while I go to school for my license.

07:35.855 --> 07:37.523
Not everybody gets that deal.

07:37.590 --> 07:38.991
I realize that now.

07:39.926 --> 07:41.561
And I never should have dropped out.

07:41.627 --> 07:42.895
You have the talent,

07:42.962 --> 07:44.831
so, I thought
I could take a chance on you.

07:44.897 --> 07:46.465
Well, since you feel that way,

07:46.532 --> 07:49.035
I was hoping
that you would give me my job back.

07:49.101 --> 07:52.305
Look, I even paid to enroll in classes.

07:52.371 --> 07:54.006
I've got the receipt right here.

07:54.073 --> 07:57.443
Honestly, Niecy, I don't feel comfortable
taking another chance.

07:57.510 --> 07:58.678
I can't afford to.

08:01.247 --> 08:02.315
Look...

08:03.216 --> 08:05.051
this is important to me.

08:05.117 --> 08:06.953
When something is truly important,

08:07.019 --> 08:09.755
we do the work and we don't make excuses.

08:09.822 --> 08:11.457
It's not an excuse.

08:13.292 --> 08:15.761
You were a single mother.
You know how hard it is.

08:15.828 --> 08:17.496
Yes, I do,

08:17.563 --> 08:20.566
and I still found a way
to be a mom and go to school.

08:20.633 --> 08:22.768
If this is what you want
for you and your kids,

08:22.835 --> 08:24.871
you'll find a way to do both...

08:24.937 --> 08:26.105
at some other salon.

08:26.706 --> 08:28.507
Now, if you will excuse me,

08:28.574 --> 08:30.509
I have to get ready for my first client.

08:36.382 --> 08:38.451
Protest is telling the truth in public,

08:38.517 --> 08:41.787
that we use our bodies and our voices
to tell the truth in the street.

08:41.854 --> 08:44.624
Be mindful that we aren't born woke.
Something wakes us up.

08:45.191 --> 08:47.927
It's important to remember
that activism, that protest,

08:47.994 --> 08:49.195
is not only in the street.

08:49.262 --> 08:52.231
It's not only retweeting a hashtag
or wearing a t-shirt,

08:52.298 --> 08:53.799
or standing outside,

08:53.866 --> 08:55.835
but a movement is many things.

08:55.902 --> 08:57.503
- And as we move forward...
- Faggot.

08:58.104 --> 09:00.840
As we... move forward,

09:01.440 --> 09:04.243
it's important to remember
that we take the truth everywhere,

09:04.310 --> 09:06.913
to the dinner table,
in our schools, in our churches...

09:06.979 --> 09:09.015
Nah, what we need is a real leader.

09:09.081 --> 09:10.516
Yeah.

09:11.250 --> 09:13.586
Thank you, Patrick Patterson,
for the invitation.

09:18.190 --> 09:21.460
DeRay Mckesson, a powerful voice
from the Black Lives Matter movement,

09:21.527 --> 09:25.164
coming here from Baltimore to mobilize,
motivate us and help us speak our truth.

09:25.231 --> 09:27.133
Let's all show him some more gratitude.

09:36.175 --> 09:39.512
Tying that workout story
to chronic back pain...

09:39.578 --> 09:40.980
that was fresh.

09:41.547 --> 09:42.949
It was Justin's idea, wasn't it?

09:44.483 --> 09:47.687
I suppose that's why
he's a senior producer, the fresh ideas.

09:47.753 --> 09:50.389
I thought he got the job
'cause Ronda wanted another black.

09:51.424 --> 09:52.892
I think they knew each other.

09:52.959 --> 09:54.293
But you know...

09:55.061 --> 09:57.196
Justin's a smart producer.

09:57.263 --> 09:59.265
Yeah. Isn't his mother white?

10:00.099 --> 10:01.834
I don't... know.

10:02.501 --> 10:04.503
Excuse me, Dani?

10:04.570 --> 10:07.373
I'm sure that a woman
with your elite background

10:07.440 --> 10:10.176
doesn't mean to suggest
that Justin's intelligence

10:10.242 --> 10:13.145
is attributable to his mother
being Caucasian, right?

10:13.212 --> 10:16.182
Because that comment
would be incendiary,

10:16.248 --> 10:17.516
and flat-out racist.

10:17.583 --> 10:20.720
No, that's not what I meant at all.
I was referring to his blue eyes.

10:20.786 --> 10:23.522
You know, for once,
I really wish that I could make

10:23.589 --> 10:25.358
an observation about a person of color

10:25.424 --> 10:26.926
and it not be labeled as racist.

10:26.993 --> 10:28.227
Bullshit!

10:28.294 --> 10:29.862
Yeah, I'm gonna call it.

10:29.929 --> 10:31.630
I'm gonna go ahead and call bullshit!

10:31.697 --> 10:35.334
And not that his racial background
is any of your concern,

10:35.401 --> 10:37.937
but both
of Justin Talbot's parents are black.

10:38.004 --> 10:40.673
So, contrary to what your narrow mind
might believe,

10:40.740 --> 10:43.309
white people do not have
a monopoly on unique eye color

10:43.376 --> 10:45.111
any more than they do on intelligence,

10:45.177 --> 10:48.247
which is a fact that you drive home
on a regular basis.

10:48.314 --> 10:52.218
So, the next time you get the urge
to exercise "free speech,"

10:52.284 --> 10:54.587
by unclogging
that verbal diarrhea factory

10:54.653 --> 10:57.189
you call a mouth and spewing
your partisan bullshit

10:57.256 --> 10:59.091
all over this studio,

10:59.158 --> 11:02.028
do us all a favor and shut the hell up,

11:02.094 --> 11:04.764
you ill-mannered, over-privileged,

11:04.830 --> 11:07.066
under-educated simpleton!

11:07.133 --> 11:08.434
Shut up!

11:33.325 --> 11:36.295
The fall-out from this mess
is going to cost us viewers,

11:36.362 --> 11:39.131
which means lower ratings,
which means lower revenue.

11:39.198 --> 11:42.735
So, when I get upstairs,
we need to talk to Legal.

11:48.707 --> 11:49.875
How bad is it?

11:49.942 --> 11:52.545
Girl, first tell me... are you okay?

11:52.611 --> 11:55.414
No. No. You know, I never thought
I would actually miss

11:55.481 --> 11:58.184
the days when racism
was administered covertly,

11:58.250 --> 12:01.454
you know,
'cause this president, he has...

12:01.520 --> 12:03.989
he has encouraged
the dim-witted radicals

12:04.056 --> 12:06.625
to just walk on over
and start shit with me.

12:06.692 --> 12:09.995
And you know what really sucks
is when you're branded unreasonable,

12:10.062 --> 12:13.532
or "the angry black woman,"
or, "gosh, she's so overly sensitive,"

12:13.599 --> 12:16.836
when you are actually offended
when someone is spouting off

12:16.902 --> 12:18.471
with their racist opinions.

12:18.537 --> 12:22.241
But we live in a free country
where everyone is able to just...

12:22.308 --> 12:24.376
speak their truth, right?

12:25.511 --> 12:27.646
By all accounts, you are correct.

12:27.713 --> 12:32.284
And Justin and I just had
a fricking win with Garrett

12:32.351 --> 12:34.186
with that last story and now...

12:35.821 --> 12:36.856
I go and do this.

12:36.922 --> 12:39.625
I'll go to Garrett's office
to assess right now.

12:40.359 --> 12:43.796
Girl, while I'm there,
regain your composure,

12:44.697 --> 12:48.100
then step out of here
like you're the anchor of this show.

12:51.537 --> 12:52.571
Thank you.

12:55.674 --> 12:57.843
- Great hearing you live.
- It's great to see you.

12:57.910 --> 13:01.046
I've heard so much about the work
you're doing in Atlanta, keep it up.

13:01.113 --> 13:04.283
I know there's a lot of work to do.
Black tutors have been talking you up.

13:04.350 --> 13:06.385
I don't know what that means,
but I thank you.

13:06.452 --> 13:09.255
Just trying to do my part.
Excuse me for a minute.

13:13.225 --> 13:14.760
What's your name, man?

13:15.394 --> 13:16.762
Jovan.

13:17.229 --> 13:19.532
It looked like you had an issue
with today's speech.

13:19.598 --> 13:23.035
- It's still a free country, right?
- If we are vigilant, it'll stay that way.

13:23.102 --> 13:25.337
There's a right and wrong way
to voice opposition.

13:25.404 --> 13:26.438
Nah, I get it.

13:26.505 --> 13:29.241
You think I'm just some thug
you can school about tactics.

13:29.308 --> 13:31.777
No, I'd actually like to hear
what you have to say.

13:31.844 --> 13:35.247
No, I would. How about we go grab
a bite to eat and we can talk about it?

13:35.848 --> 13:37.016
Get some real food.

13:37.983 --> 13:39.685
- You buying?
- Yeah, I'm buying.

13:41.654 --> 13:44.857
All right. What are we talking,
pizza or burgers?

13:44.924 --> 13:46.492
Whatever you prefer.

13:47.259 --> 13:51.397
Niecy, you're good at hair,
so just do hair.

13:51.463 --> 13:53.933
But I don't wanna do my friends' weaves

13:53.999 --> 13:55.701
in my grandmother's basement.

13:56.302 --> 13:58.637
A chair at a salon would make me legit,

13:59.138 --> 14:00.506
get me clientele.

14:00.573 --> 14:02.374
Well, doesn't your mother do hair?

14:02.441 --> 14:03.776
Why don't you just ask her?

14:03.842 --> 14:05.711
You know, I wanted to see

14:05.778 --> 14:08.047
how long it would take her to reach out

14:08.113 --> 14:09.882
if I stopped calling,

14:09.949 --> 14:11.317
just as an experiment.

14:11.383 --> 14:12.651
And how long has it been?

14:12.718 --> 14:14.153
Going on three months now.

14:14.620 --> 14:16.822
Damn. Sorry, girl.

14:17.856 --> 14:21.660
- Your mom's starting to act like mine.
- I know, it's just so frustrating

14:21.727 --> 14:22.928
'cause I need this job.

14:22.995 --> 14:26.265
Now Claudia's starting to look at me
like I'm some screw-up like my dad.

14:26.332 --> 14:29.235
- What? She said you were a screw-up?
- She didn't have to.

14:29.902 --> 14:32.071
She knows about my dad's drug trouble.

14:33.172 --> 14:35.407
Niecy, from where I'm sitting,

14:35.474 --> 14:36.909
you're not a screw-up.

14:36.976 --> 14:38.644
You've gotta get that out of your head.

14:39.211 --> 14:41.513
That's where it is, in your head.

14:41.580 --> 14:43.916
- I know.
- You sure?

14:44.783 --> 14:48.554
'Cause it seems like the only person
that thinks you're a screw-up is you.

14:53.025 --> 14:54.860
Wait. Wait a minute.

14:54.927 --> 14:56.495
What happened? What?

14:58.597 --> 15:01.400
Well, when are you gonna know more?

15:03.736 --> 15:06.505
I can't, honey. I'm at work right now.

15:06.572 --> 15:09.475
You can use my office,
if you need some privacy.

15:11.143 --> 15:12.244
Okay.

15:21.120 --> 15:25.024
Hey. So, I just left Garrett's office.

15:25.090 --> 15:27.926
- What do you wanna hear first?
- Let's start with the good news.

15:27.993 --> 15:30.529
Garrett and I are smoothing
things over with HR.

15:30.596 --> 15:31.697
Thank God.

15:32.298 --> 15:34.166
Okay... The bad?

15:34.233 --> 15:37.569
Garrett's most concerned
about a potential PR problem.

15:37.636 --> 15:40.572
We just got out of hot water
with the whole Ronda debacle,

15:40.639 --> 15:42.374
and an hour after shooting a spot

15:42.441 --> 15:45.711
promoting the GDU family,
you and a new colleague are going at it.

15:45.778 --> 15:48.514
But what happened
was within the GDU walls,

15:48.580 --> 15:51.517
- there's no pictures or video, so...
- People talk.

15:53.185 --> 15:54.987
That, they do.

15:55.954 --> 15:59.625
Okay, well, let's... Let's put our heads
together and strategize a solution.

15:59.692 --> 16:02.294
I already offered Garrett one
and he's down.

16:02.361 --> 16:03.962
Do I even wanna know?

16:04.029 --> 16:05.964
Your upcoming house warming party.

16:06.031 --> 16:08.133
Garrett wants me to get a photographer

16:08.200 --> 16:10.035
from "Entertainment Weekly" to be there

16:10.102 --> 16:12.504
to promote the GDU family thing.

16:12.571 --> 16:14.940
That means everyone
would be there, including Dani.

16:15.507 --> 16:18.844
Garrett will be in Silicon Valley
meeting with Zuckerberg for "Tech Week,"

16:18.911 --> 16:20.446
but everyone else, yes.

16:20.512 --> 16:22.748
It'll be a party full of people
that I don't like.

16:22.815 --> 16:25.084
And it's not like they'd come
after what happened.

16:25.150 --> 16:27.353
That brings me
to the second part of the deal.

16:27.419 --> 16:28.654
God, there's more.

16:28.721 --> 16:31.290
You're gonna have
to apologize, in public,

16:31.357 --> 16:33.058
to the entire crew.

16:34.426 --> 16:37.062
You need to convince everybody
you're genuinely sorry.

16:40.899 --> 16:44.103
- Who DeRay gets with is his business.
- Nah, he's in the front lines.

16:44.169 --> 16:46.538
He's making it my business.
How we gonna mobilize,

16:46.605 --> 16:48.741
like MLK when we got some homo
running the show?

16:48.807 --> 16:50.008
You really believe that?

16:50.075 --> 16:53.712
With the challenges facing Black people
today, the stakes are too high.

16:53.779 --> 16:55.547
If we wanna mobilize the masses,

16:55.614 --> 16:57.516
we can't afford
someone like that leading.

16:57.983 --> 17:00.619
Do you know the brainchild
behind the March on Washington?

17:00.686 --> 17:03.222
- Martin Luther King.
- Wrong, it was Bayard Rustin.

17:03.756 --> 17:06.358
Rustin was one
of Dr. King's closest advisors.

17:06.425 --> 17:07.760
He was also openly gay.

17:10.095 --> 17:12.831
If he was so open,
how come I never heard of him?

17:13.365 --> 17:15.234
Dr. King needed to keep that under wraps.

17:15.300 --> 17:17.469
But if Dr. King thought
like you and your boys,

17:17.536 --> 17:19.304
there wouldn't have even been a march.

17:19.371 --> 17:23.876
See, it'll be a great day when we can
convince everyone to support the cause,

17:23.942 --> 17:26.044
even if they don't agree
with their sexuality.

17:26.111 --> 17:28.013
But that day ain't here yet, so...

17:28.080 --> 17:30.549
you may not like it,
but that's how it is.

17:31.950 --> 17:35.721
Listen, we have an old saying in NA.

17:35.788 --> 17:37.656
- NA?
- Narcotics Anonymous.

17:38.390 --> 17:40.292
Take what you like, and leave the rest.

17:41.026 --> 17:42.161
What's that mean?

17:42.227 --> 17:45.030
There are tons of people involved
with "Black Lives Matter,"

17:45.097 --> 17:47.032
so many others you can identify with.

17:47.099 --> 17:49.301
If you don't like DeRay,
find someone else.

17:49.368 --> 17:52.171
You said it yourself,
there's important work to be done.

17:52.237 --> 17:54.406
So, you're gonna let DeRay
stop you from doing it?

